            "summary": "The U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit upheld a district court's decision in favor of Moderna, Inc. in a patent dispute with Alnylam Pharmaceuticals Inc. over mRNA-based COVID-19 vaccine technology, including the Spikevax COVID-19 vaccine. The court ruled that Alnylam had defined \"branched alkyl\" in a way that excluded Moderna's vaccine from infringing on their patents. The case revolved around Moderna's use of SM-102 in their vaccine formulations, with Alnylam claiming it fell within the scope of their patents. Alnylam's patents at the center of the dispute are U.S. Patent Nos. 11,246,933 and 11,382,979. Alnylam accused Moderna of violating their patents by incorporating SM-102, which enables mRNA delivery in the vaccine.",
